{{Quote|Urartu says, no humans or Droids. It's a house rule of the Contumely Club, I'm afraid.|Urartu's partner translates for the Wookiee|<ref name="RPG">[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game (first edition)|''Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game'']]</ref>}}
The '''Contumely Club''' was an entertainment location operating during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. The Club's policies denied access to [[Human/Legends|Humans]] and [[Droid/Legends|droids]]. To enforce that rule, [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] [[Bouncer (occupation)/Legends|bouncer]] [[Urartu]] was at the door, pushing out unwanted clients. A small [[Unidentified small sentient creature|alien]] translated the Wookiee's native [[Shyriiwook/Legends|Shyriiwook]]. The [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Roark Garnet/Legends|Roark Garnet]] once tried to enter the Club but was stopped by Urartu.<ref name="RPG" />

